result.execSummary:
The defendant Gabriel A. Downey was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • False Imprisonment [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 940.30.

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

superMiscConds.notes: Outstanding financial obligations shall be collected pursuant to statutory provisions, including deductions from inmate prison monies.  If reconfined or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered against the defendant and in favor of restitution victims and government entities for outstanding financial obligations.  All available enforcement actions will be used to collect the debt.  Defendant to submit DNA sample and pay the surcharge, if not previously done.

Not to enter into any bars, taverns, liquor stores, liquor department of grocery stores, the bar areas of restaurants. Defendant may not possess or consume any alcohol, nor be anywhere alcohol is available for consumption on the premises where the defendant is located.   Defendant shall have no contact, directly or indirectly, either personally, by mail, telephone or through any other person, with the victim or the victim's family.

The defendant shall comply with any treatment, evaluations and/or programming as deemed appropriate by the COMPAS assessment and the probation agent.  

Defendant must sign any releases agent deems necessary to verify defendant's compliance with probation conditions.

Undergo a full mental health evaluation, if his agent requires.

DA files an Information and defense waived the reading.  Wish to proceed to plea.  Defendant pleads guilty to Counrt 3.  Court reviews charge and penalties.  Felony warning given.  Court reviews plea questionnaire/waiver of rights/ charge/penalties. Notifies defendant if restitution is requested that there could possibly be a restitution hearing.  Defense agrees there is a factual basis in the complaint for the charge.  Court finds defendant freely, voluntarily, and intelligently waives his rights and understands the proceedings.  Counts 1,2,4,5 are dismissed and read-in.  Pre-sentence Investigation is ordered and is due to all parties by March 13, 2015 with sentencing set for March 30, 2015 at 1:30.
